properties.areaDesc: East Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 29 at 3:14AM PST until January 30 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 kt becoming southwest 15 to 25
knots in the afternoon. West wind 15 to 25 knots easing to
southwest 5 to 15 knots tonight. Winds rising to south 15 to 25
knots Thursday afternoon.

* WHERE...East Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
are expected to produce hazardous wave conditions to small craft.
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels should avoid navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THURSDAY... ...GALE WARNING IS CANCELLED
